Package com.apriori.vars Description

This package contains simple, mutable "holders" for reference types and primitives. These are lighter-weight and more intuitive than using single-element arrays for such uses. The APIs are very similar to atomic variables in java.util.concurrent, but none of these classes are thread-safe. They are meant more for use as "out parameters", where a function can modify a variable defined in the scope of its caller (all on one thread).
